Abbreviations used: AER, anterior eye row; ALE, anterior lateral eyes; ALS, anterior lateral spinnerets; AME, anterior median eyes; C, conductor; CO, copulatory openings; cy, cymbium; di, diameter; do, dorsal; E, embolus; fe, femur; fr, frontal; ICS, intercoxal sclerites—intercoxal sclerites are six small triangular or elongated sclerites surrounding the sternum, their tips penetrating between the coxae of the legs—they may be free, or fused with the sternum (

: fig. 1K); ID, insemination duct; lat, lateral; LOP, 
lorum pediculi
